track.name: There Will Never Be Another You
comments: OSCAR P AND THE PREZ IT GETS NO BETTER
dancing on the patio in late summer...fireflies...twinkling lanterns...the faint aroma of jasmine and bitter-sweet lemonade...
Noone plays like this today, he was one of the best.
wonderfully sympathetic accompany by oscar peterson and trio...op was a master musician and the best accompany any musician or vocalist could hope for...
i agree aleealski...prez had such an appealing sound...
What a sensual tone Mr. Young has.
there will never be another lester young...his contribution to jazz is invaluable and the beauty of  his playing incomparable...with much love and appreciation...RIP Prez...
lemonade and dancing on the patio in late summer...
El drama hecho arte, la languidez sonora como punto de acercamiento, arraigado al blues pero con el más profundo aire west coast. The Father of sound
